description:
Published by Titan Magazines under licence from DC Comics, this UK newstand anthology collected JLA, Superman, Green Lantern, and The Flash comics. Later the title reprinted various comics such as Justice League, Action Comics, Green Lantern and Justice League Dark from DC's The New 52.

The numbering continues from issues #1-33 when the title was named Superman Legends, and only reprinted Superman titles. As of issue #59, the title switched to a 2nd volume which can be found here (DC Universe Presents).
name: DC Universe Presents

description: This is the ultimate look into comic book creator Mike Allred's scrapbooks, sketchbooks, and secret files! Allred provides commentary throughout this visual bonanza revealing all the big breaks, influences, inspirations, turning points, friendships, collaborations, toys, merchandise, breakthroughs, setbacks and successes, all to show how a career is made and sustained. Each of the book's 64 pages is jam-packed with visual milestones. Allred shares techniques and tools he uses, as well as how he works with his wife and colorist Laura Allred in a tour of their homes and studios. It's unlikely that any publication has ever provided this amount of detail and insight into the career of an artist.
name: Vault of Michael Allred
